            "content": [
              {
                "nodeType": "text",
                "value": "Subtlety escapes this character\u2014they pound dough flat when baking, snap quills when writing, and shatter pottery with a casual grip. Tasks requiring a gentle touch, like mending a cloak or carving a wooden spoon, end in ruin. Neighbors whisper that they once broke a door by knocking too hard. They mean well, but finesse isn\u2019t their forte.",
